Structural Based Inundation Notebooks¶

Objective: Identify a location on a levee to perform a breach simulation using HEC-RAS & calculate inflow hydrograph.

In [1]:

1. Assign directories & read in data¶

In order to perform this analysis, geospatial layers must be imported into a map viewer. Layers required are

  • The river centerline of the major flooding source
  • HEC-RAS XS which will be used to identify the appropriate elevation for breach height.
  • Levee near the XS which will be breached.

2. Create an interactive map to view the data¶

  1. Zoom to the levee that will be breached. Click on one of the levee points and note the levee segment ID.
  2. Find the nearest XS. Click on the XS end point and note the XS station ID.

LeveeID = '21' 
Hydrograph = 'Levees_21.csv'

xs = '174908'
breach_point = 'US'

xs_ids = GetRasXS_ids(rasdata)
for i, x in enumerate(xs_ids): 
    if xs_ids[x] == xs: print('XS #{}, Station {}\n'.format(i ,xs_ids[x]));break
        
profiles = GetRasXS_profiles(rasdata)
printbold('XS Data/Flows Read in succesfully')

4. Read RAS geometry data & plot US XS with selected profile¶

  1. Enter the idx corresponding to the LAMP flow (1%)
  2. In the plot that appears, zoom to the levee & find a point on the XS to set as breach height
  3. Note the station at the desired location
In [11]:
profile_idx = 18 # profile index from above (wse)

# Get wse at XS for selected profile
wse = GetRasXS_wse(rasdata, profiles, profile_idx , xs_ids, xs )

# Get XS geometry 
xs_line = GetRasXS_lines(rasdata, xs_ids,  xs)

# Get XS Bank Stations
bank_stations = GetRasXS_bank_Stations(rasdata, xs_ids)
bs, be = bank_station_at_xs(bank_stations, xs, xs_line)

# Plot the XS, identify breach location
plotly_ras_xs(xs, xs_line, wse, bs, be)

5. Replot w/Breach Location & Rating Curve¶

  1. Enter in breach station

    • Read in data from the 1D RAS model.
    • Create a rating curve to translate flow to stage near the breach location.
In [12]:
ts = 2337.78 # input the XS station
te = xs_line[xs_line[0] == ts][1].values[0] # find the toe elevation (breach invert)
plotly_ras_xs(xs, xs_line, wse, bs, be, ts, te, breach_elev=True, notebook=True)

station = int(xs)
breach_elev = te

rastable = GetRasData(rasdata, station)                    # Read in ras data from station of interest
RC_Plot(rastable, xlabel = 'Flow', ylabel = 'Stage', title = 'Rating Curve for XS {}'.format(station), notebook=True)
rc_fit   = make_rc_fitline(rastable)                       # Using data from rastable, create a rc-function

RAS Data for XS 174908

6. Bring in the Base Hydrograph¶

  • For each change location in the model, there should be a 1% flow hydrograph. Read this in as the 'Base Hydrograph'
In [16]:
base_hydrograph = pd.read_csv(os.path.join(flow_dir, Hydrograph), index_col='Minutes')
base_hydrograph['stage'] = rc_fit(base_hydrograph['Stretched Hydrograph']) 
bft =  BreachFlowTrigger(base_hydrograph, breach_elev)
showplot = plot_hydrograph_days(base_hydrograph, breach_elev)
#Flow_BFT_Plot(base_hydrograph, 'Stretched Hydrograph', bft,  xlabel = None, ylabel = None, title = None, notebook=True)
printbold('Stretched Hydrograph: 1% Chance')

Stretched Hydrograph: 1% Chance

7. Compute Stage, Head & Weir Flow at XS using Base Hydrograph¶

Using the base hydrograph & the rating curve:

  1. Calculate stage time series for 1% flow above the selected breach elevation
  2. Convert the stage to head for weir flow calculation
  3. Calculate weir flow & plot
In [8]:
base_hydrograph['stage'] = rc_fit(base_hydrograph['Stretched Hydrograph']) 
df_weir = ComputeWeirFlow_num_ords(base_hydrograph, breach_elev, breach_length = 250, plot = True)
